theorem Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P1 {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (A := A) → closure A = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro hP1
  -- From `P1`, we have `closure A = closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : closure A = closure (interior A) :=
    Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1 (A := A) hP1
  -- We already know `closure (interior (closure A)) = closure (interior A)`.
  have h₂ : closure (interior (closure A)) = closure (interior A) :=
    Topology.closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_interior (A := A)
  -- Combining the two equalities gives the desired result.
  calc
    closure A = closure (interior A) := h₁
    _ = closure (interior (closure A)) := h₂.symm

theorem Topology.P2_closure_implies_P3
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 (A := closure A) → Topology.P3 (A := A) := by
  intro hP2
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  -- First, regard `x` as an element of `closure A`.
  have hx_closure : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
  -- Apply `P2` for `closure A`.
  dsimp [Topology.P2] at hP2
  have hx_int :
      x ∈ interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := hP2 hx_closure
  -- Use the monotonicity lemma to move into `interior (closure A)`.
  have h_subset :
      interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
    Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_interior_closure (A := closure A)
  exact h_subset hx_int

theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : Topology.P1 (A := A)) :
    closure (interior (closure A)) = closure (interior A) := by
  exact
    Topology.closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1
      (X := X) (A := A) h
